						Logica Iureconsultorum, et dia[e]ta Theurgorum.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Nothing makes genius more subtle than than the logic of jurisprudence and the diet of theurgy.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="right_margin" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						Diuina[e] Entelechia[e], et Ironia[e] quotidiana alimenta.
						Cu[m] his etiam Salium, apophthegmatum, epigrammatum, gnomaru[m],
						regularu[m] ( delitijs.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				The daily sustenance of divine actualization and irony. And with these, the delights found in witticisms, aphorisms,
				epigrams, maxims, and principles.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
